tegory\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=4198\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:634:\"<p>Today, I am excited to share that SeedProd is joining Awesome Motive. Awesome Motive is the management company behind the largest WordPress resource site, WPBeginner, and several popular WordPress plugins like OptinMonster, WPForms, MonsterInsights, and WP Mail SMTP. I launched SeedProd with a mission to help businesses get a head start on building their online [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-is-now-part-of-the-awesome-motive-family/\">SeedProd is Now Part of the Awesome Motive Family</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"John Turner\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4290:\"<p>Today, I am excited to share that SeedProd is joining <a href=\"https://awesomemotive.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Awesome Motive</a>.</p>\n<p>Awesome Motive is the management company behind the largest WordPress resource site, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPBeginner</a>, and several popular WordPress plugins like <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OptinMonster</a>, <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPForms</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights</a>, and <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-mail-smtp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WP Mail SMTP</a>.</p>\n<p>I launched SeedProd with a mission to help businesses get a head start on building their online presence with viral coming soon pages. Since then SeedProd has become the most popular coming soon and maintenance mode plugin for WordPress with over 800,000 active installs.</p>\n<p>It has been an amazing journey thus far, and I&#8217;m extremely thankful for the loyalty and support of the SeedProd community. With Awesome Motive&#8217;s vast resources and deep understanding of the WordPress industry, I know we&#8217;ll be able to bring even more powerful solutions to the SeedProd plugin.</p>\n<p>Since this is a BIG NEWS, you probably have a lot of questions like: how did this merger come about, what will happen to SeedProd team, will the prices stay the same, what&#8217;s coming next, etc.</p>\n<h2>Background Story</h2>\n<p>I have known <a href=\"https://syedbalkhi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Syed Balkhi</a>, founder of Awesome Motive, for multiple years. Syed has supported SeedProd since the early days by featuring it on WPBeginner. When he announced the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/news/announcing-the-wpbeginner-growth-accelerator-fund/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPBeginner accelerator fund</a> for WordPress businesses, I applied because I respect what they have built at Awesome Motive.</p>\n<p>After numerous conversations, we both agreed that a full acquisition makes more sense for SeedProd given the synergies between our products.</p>\n<p>As part of this acquisition, I will be joining Awesome Motive as a partner.</p>\n<p>When it comes to business, Syed and I share a lot of core values specifically building products that are customer-focused and easy to use.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m super excited to learn from the team and leverage their knowledge to continue making SeedProd even better.</p>\n<h2>What will happen to the SeedProd team?</h2>\n<p>SeedProd has always been a team of one (me), and I&#8217;m not going anywhere.</p>\n<p>As I mentioned, I am joining Awesome Motive as a partner and will continue to lead SeedProd.</p>\n<p>This acquisition means that we will soon be hiring and growing the SeedProd team, so we can bring more powerful solutions your way (faster).</p>\n<h2>What&#8217;s Changing on SeedProd?</h2>\n<p>Right now, nothing is changing. It&#8217;s business as usual.</p>\n<p>In the coming weeks, you will likely see a new website design.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re starting work on a revamped SeedProd builder, and I can&#8217;t wait to share all the powerful features that will bring your way!</p>\n<h2>Are you going to change prices?</h2>\n<p>We will never raise prices for existing users. If you have an active subscription of SeedProd, then you will be forever grand-fathered into your existing plan.</p>\n<p>As we add more features in the future, we may experiment with different pricing plans.</p>\n<h2>What&#8217;s Coming Next?</h2>\n<p>As I mentioned, we&#8217;re starting work on a revamped SeedProd builder, and I know you&#8217;re going to love it.</p>\n<p>We will also make tweaks to the website design to better highlight all the features that SeedProd offers.</p>\n<p>Once again, I want to thank you for your continued support of SeedProd, and I can&#8217;t wait to bring more exciting features your way.</p>\n<p>John Turner<br />\nFounder of SeedProd</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-is-now-part-of-the-awesome-motive-family/\">SeedProd is Now Part of the Awesome Motive Family</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://www.seedprod.com/seedprod-is-now-part-of-the-awesome-motive-family/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"Best WordPress Plugins – The Definitive Guide (2018)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-wordpress-plugins/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-wordpress-plugins/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 10 Apr 2018 15:59:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.seedprod.com/?p=3406\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:555:\"<p>WordPress has over 50,000 plugins and finding quality free and premium plugins can be a daunting task to say the least! I&#8217;ve been in the WordPress community for over 10 years and I know this first hand. The goal of this guide is to help you save time and money by providing you with a definitive [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/best-wordpress-plugins/\">Best WordPress Plugins &#8211; The Definitive Guide (2018)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">SeedProd</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"John Turner\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47890:\"<p>WordPress has over 50,000 plugins and finding quality free and premium plugins can be a <em>daunting task </em>to say the least! I&#8217;ve been in the WordPress community for over 10 years and I know this first hand.</p>\n<p>The goal of this guide is to help you save time and money by providing you with a definitive resource to the best free and paid plugin plugins and in various categories. No more spending hours downloading countless plugins just to test and see if they work and no more wasting money buying plugins from hack premium plugin authors.</p>\n<p><strong>Why should you listen to me?</strong></p>\n<p>I am a professional plugin developer turned business owner with over 15 years development experience and my free WordPress plugins have been downloaded over 5 million times. My <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/coming-soon/\" rel=\"noopener\">free coming soon page plugin</a> for WordPress is a top 100 plugin on WordPress.org. I have loved serving the WordPress community for the past 5+ years and want to give this guide back.</p>\n<p>Many of the plugins I&#8217;ll be recommending, I know the plugin authors behind the plugin and can vouch for all them when I say they are made by people who love the WordPress community. Many of them contribute to WordPress core, help run local meetups and WordCamps, attend WordCamp and are active members in the community.</p>\n<p>So without further ado here the <strong>Best Plugins for WordPress Guide for 2018</strong>.<br />\n<small>(Note: There are absolutely no affiliate links in this guide, it&#8217;s just my honest opinion from my many years of experience.)</small></p>\n<h2 id=\"plugin-categories\">Plugin Categories</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#backup-plugins\">Best BackUp Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#caching-plugins\">Best Caching Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#forms-plugins\">Best Forms (Contact Form) Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#calendar-plugin\">Best Calendar Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#social-sharing-plugin\">Best Social Sharing Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#best-site-migration-plugin\">Best Site Migration Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#security-plugins\">Best Security Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#lead-capture\">Best Lead Capture and Pop Up Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#page-builders\">Best Page Builder Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#image-gallery\">Best Image Gallery Plugin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#coming-soon\">Best Coming Soon and Maintenance Mode Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#google-analytics\">Best Google Analytics Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ecommerce\">Best eCommerce Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#membership\">Best Membership Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#podcasting\">Best Podcasting Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#seo\">Best SEO Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#shortlink\">Best Shortlink / Affiliate Cloaking Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#custom-content-type\">Best Custom Content Type and Fields Plugins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#misc\">Best Miscellaneous Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"backup-plugins\">Best BackUp Plugins</h2>\n<p>A Backup plugin is the number one plugin you should install on your WordPress site even before you install a <a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com\">Coming Soon plugin</a>.  Lose any amount of work or a site just once and you&#8217;ll understand why. Fortunately it&#8217;s easy to do backups with these two plugins. I recommend these plugins depending on if the site is for yourself or for a client.</p>\n<p>If you are building WordPress sites for clients I recommend <a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/?utm_source=seedprod.com\">BackupBuddy by iThemes</a>.  They have a license that lets you cost-effectively resell a backup service to your clients.  For example, you can backup up to fifty sites for just $150 per year. Plus you can bring your own object storage like Amazon S3 which makes it super cheap to store tons of data.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/\">BackUpBuddy by iThemes</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/\">Pro Version</a></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://ithemes.com/purchase/backupbuddy/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3751 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"Best Backup Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin-400x130.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/backupbuddy-backup-plugin-768x249.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a><br />\nIf you just have one site I recommend <a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\">VaultPress by Automattic</a>. This is what I personally use on this site and it&#8217;s a set it and forget it solution. Backups are stored offsite by <a href=\"https://automattic.com/\">Automattic</a> and restores are as easy as one click. Pricing starts at just $3.50 a month.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\">VaultPress by Automattic</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\">Pro Version</a></span><a href=\"https://vaultpress.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3752 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress.jpg\" alt=\"Best Backup Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress-400x130.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/vaultpress-768x249.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#plugin-categories\">↑ Back to Plugin Categories</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"caching-plugins\">Best Caching Plugins</h2>\n<p>A caching plugin is another essential plugin you must have, especially if your host does not provide any caching. One of the best caching plugins out there is <a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\">WPRocket</a> and it&#8217;s what I use on this site. It has an excellent feature set and is very well supported and yes, it does make your website like a Rocket! :)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\"><strong>WPRocket</strong></a> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\">Pro Version</a></span><a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3744 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket.jpg\" alt=\"Best Caching Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket-400x143.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wp-rocket-768x275.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you are looking for a free just page caching plugin than look no further than <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\">WP Super Cache</a>. It has a lot fewer features than WP-Rocket but gets the job done.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\"><strong>WP Super Cache</strong></a> <span class=\"label label-success\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\">Free Version</a></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-super-cache/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3745 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250.png\" alt=\"Best Caching Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"264\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250.png 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-400x137.png 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-768x263.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Some people might say, what about <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/\">W3 Total Cache</a>. Well since this is my honest opinion I have had tons of issues with this plugin mostly due to the complexity and end users not knowing how to use it. If you are super technically maybe you&#8217;d enjoy it.</p>\n<p><a href=\"#plugin-categories\">↑ Back to Plugin Categories</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"#forms-plugins\">Best Forms (Contact Form) Plugins</h2>\n<p>OK, this one is hard. I&#8217;m going to list 4 plugins and it&#8217;s really hard to go wrong with any of these. They all will get the job done when it comes to creating simple contact forms to complex forms. I personally use <a href=\"https://www.gravityforms.com/\">Gravity Forms</a> because I have been using a WordPress a long time and they were the only ones that existed when I got into the market.</p>\n<p>So first up <a href=\"https://www.gravityforms.com/\">Gravity Form</a>. Gravity Forms is the oldest among the form plugins listed. But it&#8217;s still a tried and true solution. It has never failed me.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.gravityforms.com/\">Gravity Forms</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://www.gravityforms.com/\">Pro Version</a></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.gravityforms.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3748 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/gravity-forms.jpg\" alt=\"Best Forms Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"183\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/gravity-forms.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/gravity-forms-400x95.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/gravity-forms-768x182.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Next, we have <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WPForms</a>. It&#8217;s the new kid on the block but it was created by <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/about-us/\">Jared Atchison, Syed Balkhi and Thomas Griffin</a>. I know these guys personally and I can say that anything they make is going to be awesome.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WPForms</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-success\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpforms-lite/\">Free Version</a></span> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">Pro Version</a></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3749 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"Best Forms Plugin\" width=\"772\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wpforms.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wpforms-400x124.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/wpforms-768x238.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Looking for a great free Forms plugin? Than <a href=\"https://ninjaforms.com/\">Ninja Forms</a> by <a href=\"http://jameslaws.com/\">James Laws</a> and team is an excellent choice. They have a unique form builder experience and provide add-ons for advanced functionality.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ninjaforms.com/\"><strong>Ninja Forms</strong></a> <span class=\"label label-success\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ninja-forms/\">Free Version</a></span> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://ninjaforms.com/pricing/\">Pro Version</a></span><strong><a href=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/ninja-forms.jpg\"><br />\n</a><a href=\"https://ninjaforms.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3750 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/ninja-forms.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"772\" height=\"258\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/ninja-forms.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/ninja-forms-400x134.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/ninja-forms-768x257.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></strong></p>\n<p>While I have personally never used this forms plugin I know many people including many of my customers who do and  I have only heard good things about it. Plus the owners behind the company, <a href=\"http://strategy11.com/about/\">Steve and Stephanie</a>, are great people.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://formidableforms.com/\">Formidable</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-success\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/formidable/\">Free Version</a></span> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://formidableforms.com/\">Pro Version</a></span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://formidableforms.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3756 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/formidable.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"772\" height=\"213\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/formidable.jpg 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/formidable-400x110.jpg 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/formidable-768x212.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#plugin-categories\">↑ Back to Plugin Categories</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"#calendar-plugin\">Best Calendar Plugins</h2>\n<p>When it comes to a calendar plugin I generally just <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-add-google-calendar-in-wordpress/\">embed a Google Calendar</a> in the WordPress page or post. But sometimes Google Calendar is not the best solution and you need a native calendar solution for WordPress. For example, a university I worked at needed an Academic Calendar. The best plugin to do the job with free and pro version is&#8230;</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a></strong> <span class=\"label label-success\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\">Free Version</a></span> <span class=\"label label-primary\"><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/product/wordpress-events-calendar-pro/\">Pro Version</a></span><br />\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/the-events-calendar/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3757 size-full\" src=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"772\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-1.png 772w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-1-400x130.png 400w, https://www.seedprod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/banner-772x250-1-768x249.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"#plugin-categories\">↑ Back to Plugin Categories</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"social-sharing-plugin\">Best Social Sharing Plugins</h2>\n<p>So everyone wants to add social sharing buttons to their blog post right? Well most people do, if you are one of those people then check out thes